Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,4,1);
$v = $a + random(1,5,1);
$c = "-1 + 2*$v/$a";

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

The average value of the function \( v(x) = $a x \) on the
interval \([1,c]\) is equal to $v.  Find \(c\) if \(c > 1\).
$PAR
\( c = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( Compute("$c")->cmp() );
#ANS(num_cmp( $c ) );

$a2 = ( $a/2 == int($a/2) ) ? $a/2 : "$a\over 2";
if ( $a/2 == int($a/2) ) {
   $a2c1 = "$a2\over c-1";
   $c1a2 = "c-1\over $a2";
} else {
   $a2c1 = "$a\over 2(c-1)";
   $c1a2 = "2(c-1)\over $a";
}

$num = 2*$v;
if ( $a == 2 || ( $a == 4 && $v/2 != int($v/2) ) ) {
   $v2a = $v;
   $v2aa = $v2a - 1;
} elsif ( $a == 4 ) {
   $v2a = $v/2;
   $v2aa = $v2a - 1;
} elsif ( $a == 3 && $v/3 == int($v/3) ) {
   $v2a = 2*$v/$a;
   $v2aa = $v2a - 1;
} else {  
   $v2 = 2*$v;
   $v2a = "\frac{$v2}{$a}";
   $v2aa = "$v2a - 1";
}

$a2d = ( $a2 == 1 ) ? '' : $a2;

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

The average value of \(v(x)\) on the interval \([1,c]\) is 
\[ {1\over c-1}\int_1^c $a x dx = 
   {1\over c-1}\left( {$a2d} x^2\bigg|_1^c \right) =
   {$a2c1}(c^2 - 1) = $v.
\]
Dividing by \($a2c1\), we get \(c^2 - 1 = $v({$c1a2})\), or 
\(c^2 - 1 = $v2a (c - 1)\).  This is the same as 
\[ c^2 - $v2a c + ($v2a - 1) = 0. \]
This factors as 
\[ (c - 1)(c - $v2aa) = 0, \]
so that the solution \(c > 1\) is \( c = $v2aa \).

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


